## Feature Completion Checklist

A feature is ONLY complete when ALL of these are done:

- [ ] Backend implementation complete
- [ ] Frontend implementation complete
- [ ] Backend unit tests pass
- [ ] API integration tests pass
- [ ] Frontend component tests pass
- [ ] **End-to-end test passes** (user clicks button → API call → database → response → UI update)
- [ ] Manual testing in browser confirms expected behavior
- [ ] Code reviewed for duplicates and clutter
- [ ] Documentation updated

### E2E Test Example

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Proper E2E test
test('User can create and view a document', async () => {
  // Frontend action
  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/admin/documents')
  await page.click('button:has-text("New Document")')
  await page.fill('input[name="title"]', 'Test Doc')
  await page.fill('textarea[name="content"]', 'Test content')
  await page.click('button:has-text("Save")')
  
  // Wait for API call and DB save
  await page.waitForSelector('text=Document created successfully')
  
  // Verify in UI
  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/admin/documents')
  await expect(page.locator('text=Test Doc')).toBeVisible()
  
  // Verify in backend
  const response = await fetch('http://localhost:8000/api/documents')
  const docs = await response.json()
  expect(docs.find(d => d.title === 'Test Doc')).toBeDefined()
})
```

